	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64158293"><p>The motivation for relativity wasn't explaining astronomical observations. If it had only been Mercury's orbit, an extra planet too close to the sun to detect is (and was) a much simpler explanation than special relativity. The motivation for special relativity was reconciling an apparent inconsistency in Maxwell's electromagnetism, and the invariance of the speed of light observed by experiments like Michaelson and Morely. Relativity famously *also* explained the anomalous orbit of Mercury. Relativity expl<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
